<paragraph id="553F36FEFF85F93EEDE74D46FB80FC76" blockId="6.[136,1452,338,941]" pageId="6" pageNumber="73">
Notes:—Multi-locus phylogenetic analyses indicated that our isolate CGMCC3.19590 clusters in a clade closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="92804D7DFF85F93EEDA24D63FE11FC9B" box="[248,404,806,833]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Chaetosphaeriaceae" genus="Chloridium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Chaetosphaeriales" pageId="6" pageNumber="73" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="gonytrichii">
<emphasis id="67F4EAECFF85F93EEDA24D63FE11FC9B" box="[248,404,806,833]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="73">C. gonytrichii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with high statistical support (
<figureCitation id="CDBB2A7BFF85F93EEFBB4D62FCA7FC9B" box="[737,802,806,832]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[136,229,1824,1846]" captionTargetBox="[199,1408,886,1786]" captionTargetId="figure-270@3.[151,1436,868,1796]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Phylogram of RAxML analysis based on a combined ITS and LSU sequence dataset within Chloridium. Adautomilanezia caesalpiniae was used as outgroup. Bootstrap support values for Maximum likelihood and Maximum parsimony greater than 50%, and Bayesian posterior probabilities equal to or greater than 0.8 are indicated at the nodes (ML/BI/MP). Type strains are highlighted by a “*”, and our strain is in bold." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6605363" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6605363/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="73">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). Morphologically, the conidial dimensions in the present study fit exactly with those in 
<bibRefCitation id="31114B0FFF85F93EEC844D0FFD24FCBF" author="Bao, D. F. &amp; Hyde, K. D. &amp; McKenzie, E. H. &amp; Jeewon, R. &amp; Su, H. Y. &amp; Nalumpang, S. &amp; Luo, Z. L." box="[478,673,842,869]" pageId="6" pageNumber="73" pagination="669" refId="ref4554" refString="Bao, D. F., Hyde, K. D., McKenzie, E. H., Jeewon, R., Su, H. Y., Nalumpang, S. &amp; Luo, Z. L. (2021) Biodiversity of Lignicolous Freshwater Hyphomycetes from China and Thailand and Description of Sixteen Species. Journal of Fungi 7 (8): 669. https: // doi. org / 10.3390 / jof 7080669" type="journal article" year="2021">
Bao 
<emphasis id="67F4EAECFF85F93EEF494D0FFDC0FCBF" box="[531,581,842,868]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="73">et al</emphasis>
. (2021)
</bibRefCitation>
. Therefore, this species was identified as 
<taxonomicName id="92804D7DFF85F93EE92C4D0FFA97FCBF" box="[1142,1298,842,869]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Chaetosphaeriaceae" genus="Chloridium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Chaetosphaeriales" pageId="6" pageNumber="73" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="gonytrichii">
<emphasis id="67F4EAECFF85F93EE92C4D0FFA97FCBF" box="[1142,1298,842,869]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="73">C. gonytrichii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by combined morphology and phylogenetic analyses. Moreover, this report of this poorly known taxon extends its distribution to southwest 
<collectingCountry id="2D97766EFF85F93EEDA54DD6FEC7FC77" box="[255,322,914,940]" name="China" pageId="6" pageNumber="73">China</collectingCountry>
from its original location in 
<collectingCountry id="2D97766EFF85F93EEFDE4DD7FC8CFC77" box="[644,777,914,941]" name="Puerto Rico" pageId="6" pageNumber="73">Puerto Rico</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="31114B0FFF85F93EEE4D4DD6FC7CFC76" author="Reblova, M. &amp; Miller, A. N. &amp; Rossman, A. Y. &amp; Seifert, K. A. &amp; Crous, P. W. &amp; Hawksworth, D. L. &amp; Abdel-Wahab, M. A. &amp; Cannon, P. F. &amp; Daranagama, D. A. &amp; Wilhelm, D. B. Z. &amp; Huang, S. K. &amp; Hyde, K. D. &amp; Jayawardena, R. &amp; Jaklitsch, W. &amp; Jones, E. B. G. &amp; Ju, Y. M. &amp; Judith, C. &amp; Maharachchikumbura, S. S. N. &amp; Pang, K. L. &amp; Petrini, L. E. &amp; Raja, H. A. &amp; Romero, A. I. &amp; Shearer, C. &amp; Senanayake, I. C. &amp; Voglmayr, H. &amp; Weir, B. S. &amp; Wijayawarden, N. N." box="[791,1017,914,941]" pageId="6" pageNumber="73" pagination="131 - 153" refId="ref6186" refString="Reblova, M., Miller, A. N., Rossman, A. Y., Seifert, K. A., Crous, P. W., Hawksworth, D. L., Abdel-Wahab, M. A., Cannon, P. F., Daranagama, D. A., Wilhelm, D. B. Z., Huang, S. K., Hyde, K. D., Jayawardena, R., Jaklitsch, W., Jones, E. B. G., Ju, Y. M., Judith, C., Maharachchikumbura, S. S. N., Pang, K. L., Petrini, L. E., Raja, H. A., Romero, A. I., Shearer, C., Senanayake, I. C., Voglmayr, H., Weir, B. S. &amp; Wijayawarden, N. N. (2016) Recommendations for competing sexual-asexually typified generic names in Sordariomycetes (except Diaporthales, Hypocreales, and Magnaporthales). IMA Fungus 7 (1): 131 - 153. https: // doi. org / 10.5598 / imafungus. 2016.07.01.08" type="journal article" year="2016">
Réblová 
